{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a plate on mixing bowl lid, weigh flour onto it then set aside.","Place cheese and bread in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add polenta and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place ﬁsh, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. With floured hands, take golf ball sized amounts of fish and shape into fish or rectangles (approx. 6 cm long).","Dust fish in flour, dip in egg mix then coat in reserved breadcrumbs. Cover and refrigerate until ready to fry.","Heat oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and fry coated ﬁsh for about 4 minutes on each side until golden brown and crisp. Once cooked drain on paper towel. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g plain flour, plus more for flouring","30 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (3 cm)","30 g sliced white bread, torn in pieces","20 g polenta","400 g cod fillets, skinless, boneless or other preferred fish","2 pinches fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","olive oil, for shallow frying","2 medium eggs, beaten with 1 tsp water"]}],"id":"r105987","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-9P3yFu7qJss\/XZVQUrnisLI\/AAAAAAAAc_0\/dmlYYnM0YVApVyTjqAvL7c9ypoaJ60hXwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Kj7UFDfviRLvC6tq.png","title":"Crispy Breaded Fish","publishedAt":"2016-03-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"10.4 g","fat":"2.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"5.3 g","calories":"352 kJ \/ 84 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, paper towel, frying pan, refrigerator, hob","hintsAndTricks":["A fish shaped cookie cutter can be used to form the fish pieces."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","35m","10 portions"]}